@@dв•љв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ќ@@N

A @@Wrevenant@@N is a permanent undead minion raised from an NPC corpse
using the @@Wcast revenant@@N spell (Necromancer/Ego 70).

@@WTHE CORPSE IS THE CHASSIS@@N
  The quality of the corpse determines your revenant's power.
  A higher-level mob with better combat stats (hitroll, damroll,
  resistances, spellpower, etc.) produces a stronger revenant.
  You can then use @@Wtracks@@N to multiply those base stats further.

  @@RBETTER CORPSE = BETTER REVENANT AT EVERY STAGE.@@N

@@WLEVEL CAP@@N
  Your revenant's level is capped at the @@Wlower@@N of:
    - The corpse's original mob level
    - Your pseudo level
    - 150 (hard cap)

@@WBASIC USAGE@@N
  1. Kill a strong NPC mob
  2. @@Wcast revenant <corpse>@@N to raise it
  3. @@Wrevenant track <name>@@N to choose upgrade paths
  4. @@Wrevenant infuse <corpse>@@N to feed more corpses for soul points
  5. @@Wrevenant rankup@@N to spend soul points on track upgrades

@@WCOMMANDS@@N
  @@Wrevenant status@@N        - View stats, tracks, and soul points
  @@Wrevenant infuse <corpse>@@N- Feed a corpse for soul points
  @@Wrevenant track <name>@@N   - Set primary or secondary track
  @@Wrevenant rankup@@N         - Advance a track rank with soul points
  @@Wrevenant tracks@@N         - List all available tracks

@@WRELATED HELPS@@N
  @@Whelp revenant tracks@@N   - Detailed track descriptions
  @@Whelp revenant infuse@@N   - Soul point feeding system
  @@Whelp revenant stats@@N    - How corpse stats affect your revenant

