@@dв•љв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ќ@@N

Tracks @@Wmultiply@@N your revenant's base stats from the corpse.
A track upgrade on a powerful corpse yields much bigger gains
than the same upgrade on a weak corpse.

@@Wв”Ђв”Ђ PRIMARY TRACKS в”Ђв”Ђ@@N (5 ranks, active combat abilities)

  @@Wdread@@N   - Offensive melee.  Multiplies hitroll, damroll, crit.
            Best on corpses with high hr_mod and dr_mod.

  @@Wshadow@@N  - Evasion and ambush.  Multiplies dodge, parry, pierce.
            Best on corpses with high dodge/parry stats.

  @@Wbone@@N    - Tanking and defense.  Multiplies AC, block, HP.
            Best on corpses with high ac_mod and hp_mod.

  @@Wsoul@@N    - Spellcasting.  Multiplies spellpower, spell crit.
            Best on corpses with casting abilities and high spellpower.

  @@Wplague@@N  - DoTs and debuffs.  Level drives save DCs for
            poison, weaken, and curse effects.
            Best on high-level corpses.

  @@Wblood@@N   - Lifesteal and sustain.  Multiplies healing, hitroll.
            Best on corpses with high healing_mod and hr_mod.

@@Wв”Ђв”Ђ SECONDARY TRACKS в”Ђв”Ђ@@N (3 ranks, passive aura on master)

  @@Wwrath@@N   - Damage aura.  Master gains bonus damroll
            scaled to revenant's base damroll.

  @@Wward@@N    - Protection aura.  Master gains AC bonus
            scaled to revenant's base AC modifier.

  @@Whunger@@N  - Mana siphon.  Master regenerates mana each tick
            scaled to revenant's spellpower.

  @@Wspite@@N   - Retribution.  When master is hit, revenant
            retaliates for damage scaled to hitroll.

  @@Wwhisper@@N - Buff support.  Periodic minor buffs to master
            scaled to revenant's level.

  @@Wdecay@@N   - Debuff aura.  Enemies in combat near the
            revenant are weakened, scaled to level.

@@WTRACK MULTIPLIERS@@N

  @@WPrimary Track:@@N
    Rank 1:  x1.00  (base)
    Rank 2:  x1.10   (25 soul points)
    Rank 3:  x1.20   (75 soul points)
    Rank 4:  x1.35  (150 soul points)
    Rank 5:  x1.50  (300 soul points)

  @@WSecondary Track:@@N
    Rank 1:   5%% of stat shared to master  (free)
    Rank 2:  10%% of stat shared to master  (50 soul points)
    Rank 3:  15%% of stat shared to master (150 soul points)

@@WEXAMPLE@@N
  A dragon corpse with dr_mod=60:
    Dread rank 1: 60 damroll
    Dread rank 5: 90 damroll (x1.50)

  A rat corpse with dr_mod=3:
    Dread rank 1: 3 damroll
    Dread rank 5: 4 damroll (x1.50)

  @@RTHE CORPSE MATTERS MORE THAN THE TRACK.@@N

@@WSWITCHING TRACKS@@N
  You can switch tracks at any time, but switching @@Rresets@@N
  the rank to 1 and @@Rforfeits@@N invested soul points.
  Choose wisely!

