When you raise a revenant, it inherits the original mob's stats:

@@WSTAT               INHERITANCE@@N
  Level              Capped at your pseudo_level (max 150)
  Hitroll (hr_mod)   Inherited directly from mob template
  Damroll (dr_mod)   Inherited directly from mob template
  AC Mod (ac_mod)    Inherited directly from mob template
  HP Mod (hp_mod)    Scaled by level ratio
  Spellpower         Inherited directly from mob template
  Healing Mod        Inherited directly from mob template
  Crit / Spell Crit  Inherited directly from mob template
  Dodge / Parry      Inherited directly from mob template
  Block / Pierce     Inherited directly from mob template
  Resistances        Inherited + poison immunity added
  Susceptibilities   Inherited + holy susceptibility added
  Combat Skills      Inherited (skills, cast, def flags)
  Combat Class       Inherited (determines spell AI)

@@WUNDEAD OVERLAY@@N
  All revenants receive:
  - Poison resistance (undead immunity)
  - Holy susceptibility (undead weakness)
  - ACT_UNDEAD and ACT_PET flags
  - Permanent duration (no extract timer)

@@WWHY CORPSE QUALITY MATTERS@@N
  Track multipliers amplify the base stats.  Example:

  Dragon (hr_mod=80, dr_mod=60, ac_mod=200):
    Dread rank 5: hr=120, dr=90 вЂ” devastating melee
    Bone rank 5:  ac=300 вЂ” nearly impenetrable tank
    Wrath rank 3: master gets +9 damroll aura

  Rat (hr_mod=2, dr_mod=1, ac_mod=5):
    Dread rank 5: hr=3, dr=1 вЂ” trivial improvement
    Bone rank 5:  ac=7 вЂ” marginal defense
    Wrath rank 3: master gets +0 damroll aura

  Hunt the best corpse you can find. @@RThe corpse IS the loot.@@N
